    "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #8787.\n\nThis PR renames the existing Numba CUDA-based cooperative primitives from `cuda.coop` to `cuda.coop._experimental`, making the canonical import:\n\n```python\nimport cuda.coop._experimental as coop\n```\n\nIt also removes the tracked `cuda.cccl.cooperative.experimental` compatibility package, moves the coop tests and benchmarks under `tests/coop/_experimental/` and `benchmarks/coop/_experimental/`, and updates docs, examples, release metadata, and CI paths for the new namespace.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `python -m compileall -q python/cuda_cccl/cuda/coop python/cuda_cccl/tests/coop/_experimental python/cuda_cccl/benchmarks/coop/_experimental`\n- import smoke for `import cuda.coop._experimental as coop`, including negative checks for old `cuda.coop.numba_cuda`, `cuda.coop.block`, `cuda.coop.warp`, and `cuda.cccl.cooperative.experimental`\n- `python -m pytest -n 4 -v python/cuda_cccl/tests/coop/_experimental` (`1889 passed, 24 skipped`)\n- `python -m pytest -v python/cuda_cccl/tests/test_examples.py` (`68 passed`)\n- `pre-commit run --files ...`\n- `roborev review --branch --wait` (passed)\n- GitHub PR CI passed after rerunning two unrelated transient failures (`564` passed, `5` skipped)\n\nCo-Authored By: Codex GPT-5.5 xhigh\n",
